    <p>EMILY GUERIN, BYLINE: Back in September, the Orange County Board of Supervisors approved a new housing development called Esperanza Hills. It's 340 luxury homes on an undeveloped patch of land. It's got amazing views of hills and canyons. And Kevin Johnson thinks it's a disaster waiting to happen.</p>
    <p>KEVIN JOHNSON: This site is probably the most dangerous site in Southern California that you could pick to put 340 new families into.</p>
