    <p>(SOUNDBITE OF MUSIC)</p>
    <p>MARTIN: So there are two people claiming to be the president of Venezuela right now. And as you'd imagine, there's all kinds of chaos as a result.</p>
    <p>INSKEEP: Nicolas Maduro was re-elected president, but the Socialist government that's been in power for many, many years has been accused of rigging elections and also changing the rules when they lose. And the leader of the legislature, Juan Guaido, has declared himself the interim president.</p>
    <p>(SOUNDBITE OF ARCHIVED RECORDING)</p>
