    <p>GOMEZ: We're excited to be open to the public. This is our mission.</p>
    <p>ELLIS: Siobhan Starrs says she can't wait to hear the footsteps echoing through the entrance of the Natural History Museum.</p>
    <p>STARRS: It was a dark kind of cold, quiet space. It felt very lonely. We miss our visitors.</p>
    <p>ELLIS: The museum's director, Kirk Johnson, was on site through the shutdown, and he says it was just like the movies.</p>
    <p>KIRK JOHNSON: I was here every day. It was a big night at the museum and a big day at the museum. I was the only person on the entire third floor.</p>
    <p>ELLIS: He's really looking forward to having some company.</p>
